\q
\v 23 Keep thy heart with all diligence; 
\q For out of it are the issues of life. 
\q
\v 24 Put away from thee a wayward mouth, 
\q And perverse lips put far from thee. 
\q
\v 25 Let thine eyes look right on, 
\q And let thine eyelids look straight before thee. 
\q
\v 26 Make level the path of thy feet, 
